SIMPLE: harvest-home
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harvest-home
<hw>Har"vest-home"</hw> <pr>(-h⟦omac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The gathering and bringing home of the harvest; the time of
harvest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Showed like a stubble land at <qex>harvest-home</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The song sung by reapers at the feast made at the
close of the harvest; the feast itself.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A service of thanksgiving, at harvest time, in the
Church of England and in the Protestant Episcopal Church in the United
States.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The opportunity of gathering treasure.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harvesting</ent>⟦br⟧
